.so fork.tmac
.SS MACRO cdef_arg
.PP
Use this macro to declare each member of the function or other
declaration.
It collects arguments that will be printed out with a
.BR \&.cdef_end " or " \&.cdef_end_stacked
macro.
.PP
.gp_cdef_arg
.TP
.I type
is the data type part of an argument definition.
Use non-breaking spaces between keywords in the
.I type
argument to prevent line breaks within them:
.IP
.EX
\&.cdef_arg \(dqconst\(rs char\(rs *\(dq name
.EE
.TP
.I name
is the name part of an argument definition.
For our purposes, it is an optional argument, especially for a data
structure like an
.BR enum .
